JOHANNESBURG – Capitec, Nedbank and the PIC have been shortlisted by the Portuguese government as potential buyers of Mercantile Bank. The shortlisted bidders will be invited to engage strategically with the board and management. Official bidding will commence after this engagement. READ: PIC won’t invest in SAA: Treasury Parties will then have eight weeks to put in a binding offer. The bank serves more than 12,000 entrepreneurs in South Africa. eNCA